<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="719" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Swenson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Have informed Danish Minister here that this Government agrees with the
                            Danish Government in its interpretation of the treaty as set forth in
                            Mr. Brun’s note of April 18th.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>